'''Desktop wars''' may refer to:

* The struggle for dominance of the desktop computer market from the mid-1980s to mid-1990s between [[Classic Mac OS|Apple's classic Mac OS]], [[History of Microsoft Windows|Microsoft's Windows (DOS-based)]] and [[OS/2|IBM's OS/2]].{{Citation needed|date=July 2010}}
* The debate among [[Linux]] users and developers as to which Linux [[desktop environment]] is best; generally, the wars are fought over [[KDE]] and [[GNOME]], although alternatives such as [[Xfce]] are tossed in the mix. For the most part, it is friendly competition between the two, but occasionally, there have been cases in which aspects of the development of desktop environments have been criticised, such as by [[Linus Torvalds#Later years|Linus Torvalds]].<ref>{{cite web|title=GNOME v. KDE, December 2005 edition|url=https://lwn.net/Articles/163792/|first=Jonathan|last=Corbet|work=[[LWN.net]]|date=2005-12-13|accessdate=2010-07-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Linus versus GNOME|url=http://www.desktoplinux.com/news/NS8745257437.html|author=Steven J. Vaughan-Nichols|work=[[DesktopLinux.com]]|date=2007-02-23|accessdate=2010-07-24|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100209010328/http://www.desktoplinux.com/news/NS8745257437.html|archivedate=2010-02-09|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=KDE 4, distributors, and bleeding-edge software|url=https://lwn.net/Articles/316827/|first=Jake|last=Edge|work=[[LWN.net]]|date=2009-01-28|accessdate=2010-07-24}}</ref>

