The '''Dundee Museum of Transport''', located in [[Dundee]], [[Scotland]], officially opened to the public on 26 April 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Transport museum to open at Market Mews in April|url=http://www.thecourier.co.uk/news/local/dundee/transport-museum-to-open-at-market-mews-in-april-1.165863|publisher=[[The Courier (Dundee)]]|date=16 December 2013|accessdate=26 January 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222144600/http://www.thecourier.co.uk/news/local/dundee/transport-museum-to-open-at-market-mews-in-april-1.165863|archivedate=22 February 2014|df=}}</ref>
The museum is currently housed in temporary accommodation on Market Street (in the Market Mews). The museum's organisers hope to relocate it to permanent premises at the Maryfield Tram Depot, in the Stobswell area of the city. Currently listed on the Buildings at Risk register by the [[RCAHMS]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.buildingsatrisk.org.uk/ref_no/2329 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-01-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223015537/http://www.buildingsatrisk.org.uk/ref_no/2329 |archivedate=2014-02-23 |df= }}</ref> the premises will require extensive repairs and upgrades.

The museum's collection continues to grow apace, with donations and several restoration projects underway.
